Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pop half the @garlic cloves{4}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Add the parcel onto the potato tray and roast until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{190%grams}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(stalks and all).

Drain the @king prawns{225%grams}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing with half the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}.

Add the baby plum tomatoes, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Set aside for now.

Next, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #small saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{60%grams} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once browned, lower the heat and stir in the @tomato puree{30%grams} and half the @smoked paprika{2%sachets}, fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce along with the remaining @red wine vinegar{12%ml}. Bring to a boil and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once thickened, remove from the heat and season with salt and pepper to taste. Cover to keep warm.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

In a small bowl, combine the roasted garlic, @mayonnaise{64%grams} and @water{1%tbsp} for the mayo. Set aside.

When the potatoes have 5 mins remaining, remove the tray from the oven. Pop the @Serrano ham{2%slices} alongside. Return to the oven for the remaining time until crisp and golden, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat the @olive oil{3%tbsp} for the pil pil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the prawns. Season with salt and pepper and stir-fry for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the grated garlic and remaining paprika and stir fry, ~{1%minute} more.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle. Remove from the heat.

A few mins before everything's ready, pop the @ciabatta{2%slices} into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Reheat the chorizo sauce.

When everything's ready, break up the Serrano ham into shards.

Add the @wild rocket{40%grams} to the tomato bowl. Toss to coat in the dressing. Transfer to a #serving bowl{} and scatter over the serrano shards.

Pop the pil pil style prawns into another serving bowl. Sprinkle over half parsley.

Serve the potato chunks in a separate bowl. Drizzle over the chorizo bravas sauce and garlic aioli. Sprinkle over the remaining parsley.

Cut the ciabatta into 1cm slices and serve alongside for dipping and scooping.

Enjoy!